definitions.definition: Of the branch of the Uralic language family that includes Finnish , Estonian , Karelian , Veps , Livonian , Ingrian and Votic .
Of the hypothetical Finno-Volgaic subgrouping of the Uralic languages that includes the Baltic-Finnic, Sami, Mordvinic and Mari languages.
Of the hypothetical Finno-Permic subgrouping of the Uralic languages that includes the Finno-Volgaic and Permic languages.
